'''Academy of Korean Studies''' (한국학중앙연구원, AKS) is a South Korean research and educational institute with the purpose of establishing profound research on [[Korean culture]]. It was established on June 22, 1978, by Ministry of Education & Science Technology of South Korea (교육과학기술부).<ref name="encyber">{{cite web |url=http://www.doopedia.co.kr/doopedia/master/master.do?_method=view&MAS_IDX=101013000867325 |title=한국학중앙연구원 (The Academy of Korean Studies 韓國學中央硏究院)|publisher=[[Doosan Encyclopedia]] |accessdate=2008-04-27|language=Korean}}</ref> The Academy has dedicated to interpreting and analyzing traditional Korean culture, defining the academic identity of [[Korean studies]], and educating scholars.<ref>{{cite web|title=Presidents's Message |url=http://intl.aks.ac.kr/english/viewforum.php?f=1 |publisher=The official English site. |accessdate=2008-04-27| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080415182046/http://www.aks.ac.kr/eng_home/main/submain.asp?part_id=1&content_id=4| archivedate= 15 April 2008 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref>
